benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/xml - Upload the full catalog as XML

covered: Valid Payload scenarios: TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC12, TC13, TC16, TC17, TC18, TC19, TC20, TC22, TC24, TC29, TC30, TC31 cover successful uploads with a variety of payloads and conditions.
Invalid payload scenarios: TC08 (malformed XML), TC07 (empty header value invalid), TC09 (empty body), TC11 (extra headers tolerated), TC17 (malicious content)
gaps: Caching behavior (ETag, Cache-Control) tests are missing.
Explicit 500 Internal Server Error scenario (server/db failure beyond 503).
Explicit authorization failures beyond missing/invalid token (e.g., 401/403 in broader contexts).
Rate limiting/throttling tests beyond a single performance scenarios (TC19/TC20 only touch latency).
Pagination is not applicable to POST catalog upload; no need to test, but could consider load-focused validation beyond TC19/TC20.
recommendations: Add tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on successful POST responses.
Add explicit 500 Internal Server Error scenario to simulate database or internal service failure beyond the 503 case.
Add broader authorization tests (e.g., invalid/expired tokens causing 401/403 in more contexts).
Enhance performance tests with explicit rate-limiting/throttle validation and clearer thresholds.
